\c 1
\ms1 Introduction
\s1 Salutation
\m 
\v 1 \w Paul|strong="G3972"\w*, \w an|strong="G2532"\w* apostle—\w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w men|strong="G3588"\w* \w nor|strong="G3761"\w* \w through|strong="G1223"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w man|strong="G3498"\w*,\f + \fr 1:1 \ft Paul's apostleship did not depend upon human ordination or recognition. So what about apostleship today?\f* \w but|strong="G2532"\w* \w through|strong="G1223"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Father|strong="G3962"\w*, \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w raised|strong="G1453"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w dead|strong="G3498"\w*\f + \fr 1:1 \ft The resurrection of Jesus Christ from the dead is absolutely central to the Christian Faith (1 Corinthians 15:14,17).\f*—
\v 2 \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* brothers \w with|strong="G4862"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*,\f + \fr 1:2 \ft It would be interesting to know who those “brothers” were.\f* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* congregations \w in|strong="G2532"\w* \w Galatia|strong="G1053"\w*:\f + \fr 1:2 \ft “The congregations in Galatia”—Paul evidently intended that the letter be widely circulated. Would not each congregation want its own copy?\f*
\v 3 \w Grace|strong="G5485"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w peace|strong="G1515"\w* \w from|strong="G1515"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Father|strong="G3962"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w our|strong="G2316"\w* \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*,
\v 4 \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w gave|strong="G1325"\w* \w Himself|strong="G1438"\w*\f + \fr 1:4 \ft In John 10:17-18 Sovereign Jesus made this clear.\f* \w for|strong="G5228"\w* \w our|strong="G2316"\w* sins, \w so|strong="G2532"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w might|strong="G2532"\w* \w deliver|strong="G1807"\w* \w us|strong="G1325"\w* \w out|strong="G1537"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w this|strong="G3588"\w* \w present|strong="G1764"\w* \w malignant|strong="G4190"\w* age,\f + \fr 1:4 \ft The word ‘malignant’ properly refers to Satan, the ‘god of this world’, so “this present malignant age” presumably refers to the whole world system controlled by Satan. All human cultures have suffered satanic influence, and all true followers of Sovereign Jesus should place biblical values above those of their surrounding culture. The second (last) Adam came to recover all that the first Adam lost—precisely the will of the Father.\f* \w according|strong="G2596"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G2307"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w our|strong="G2316"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w Father|strong="G3962"\w*,
\v 5 \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w whom|strong="G3739"\w* \w be|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G1519"\w* \w glory|strong="G1391"\w* \w forever|strong="G1519"\w* \w and|strong="G1391"\w* \w ever|strong="G1519"\w*. Amen.
\s1 Paul is disappointed
\p 
\v 6 \w I|strong="G3754"\w* \w am|strong="G3588"\w* sadly \w surprised|strong="G2296"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w turning|strong="G1722"\w* away \w so|strong="G3779"\w* \w quickly|strong="G5030"\w* \w from|strong="G3588"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w called|strong="G2564"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w by|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w grace|strong="G5485"\w* \w of|strong="G5485"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*, \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w a|strong="G1519"\w* \w different|strong="G2087"\w* \w gospel|strong="G2098"\w*
\v 7 —\w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* mere variation, \w but|strong="G2532"\w* \w certain|strong="G5100"\w* \w people|strong="G1510"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* unsettling \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w wanting|strong="G2309"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w distort|strong="G3344"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Gospel|strong="G2098"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*.
\v 8 \w Now|strong="G2532"\w* \w even|strong="G2532"\w* \w if|strong="G1437"\w* \w we|strong="G2249"\w*, \w or|strong="G2228"\w* \w an|strong="G2532"\w* angel \w out|strong="G1537"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w heaven|strong="G3772"\w*, \w should|strong="G2532"\w* \w preach|strong="G2097"\w* \w any|strong="G1437"\w* \w other|strong="G3739"\w* \w gospel|strong="G2097"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w than|strong="G2228"\w* \w what|strong="G3739"\w* \w we|strong="G2249"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w preached|strong="G2097"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*, \w let|strong="G1510"\w* \w him|strong="G3739"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* accursed!
\v 9 \w As|strong="G5613"\w* \w we|strong="G3739"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w just|strong="G5613"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w*, \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w here|strong="G1510"\w* emphatically repeat: \w If|strong="G1487"\w* \w anyone|strong="G5100"\w* preaches \w any|strong="G5100"\w* \w other|strong="G3739"\w* \w gospel|strong="G2097"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w than|strong="G3844"\w* \w what|strong="G3739"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w received|strong="G3880"\w*, \w let|strong="G1510"\w* \w him|strong="G3739"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* accursed!!\f + \fr 1:9 \ft ‘Other gospels’ would seem to be in plentiful supply; those who promote them are under a curse. Note that Paul is claiming to be competent to define the only true Gospel of Christ, and he can only do so genuinely by divine inspiration.\f*
\p 
\v 10 \w Am|strong="G1510"\w* \w I|strong="G1063"\w* \w just|strong="G3588"\w* \w now|strong="G1510"\w* appealing \w to|strong="G2212"\w* \w men|strong="G1401"\w*, \w or|strong="G2228"\w* \w to|strong="G2212"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*?\f + \fr 1:10 \ft Since it is God who applies the curse, he is appealing to God to back him up. I myself do this habitually.\f* \w Or|strong="G2228"\w* \w am|strong="G1510"\w* \w I|strong="G1063"\w* \w trying|strong="G2212"\w* \w to|strong="G2212"\w* please \w men|strong="G1401"\w*? \w You|strong="G1487"\w* see, \w if|strong="G1487"\w* \w I|strong="G1063"\w* \w were|strong="G1510"\w* \w still|strong="G2089"\w* pleasing \w men|strong="G1401"\w* \w I|strong="G1063"\w* \w would|strong="G2316"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w a|strong="G1510"\w* \w slave|strong="G1401"\w* \w of|strong="G2316"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*.\f + \fr 1:10 \ft Oops! Come on Paul, you cannot be serious. Do you really mean that pleasing men and being a slave of Christ are mutually exclusive? On the basis of my experience I would have to agree with Paul, with the understanding that fellow slaves are not included in the ‘pleasing men’. (When I am pleasing Christ His other slaves should be pleased as well.)\f*
\ms1 Paul's credentials
\p 
\v 11 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* want \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w to|strong="G2596"\w* \w know|strong="G1107"\w*, brothers, \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w the|strong="G1161"\w* \w Gospel|strong="G2098"\w* \w preached|strong="G2097"\w* \w by|strong="G5259"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w according|strong="G2596"\w* \w to|strong="G2596"\w* \w man|strong="G3756"\w*;
\v 12 \w because|strong="G1223"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w did|strong="G3880"\w* \w not|strong="G3761"\w* \w receive|strong="G3880"\w* \w it|strong="G1063"\w* \w from|strong="G3844"\w* \w any|strong="G3761"\w* man, \w nor|strong="G3761"\w* \w was|strong="G2424"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w taught|strong="G1321"\w* \w it|strong="G1063"\w*; \w rather|strong="G3844"\w* \w it|strong="G1063"\w* \w came|strong="G1223"\w* \w through|strong="G1223"\w* \w a|strong="G1223"\w* revelation \w from|strong="G3844"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*.\f + \fr 1:12 \ft I follow what I understand to be the best line of transmission (though in a minority here, 30%) that reads ‘Christ’ without ‘Jesus’. I take it that ‘Christ’ is in the ablative case: ‘from’ rather than ‘of’. Paul is claiming revelation—this is the plain meaning of verses 11-12. Saul of Tarsus got his training in Judaism at the feet of Gamaliel, but his understanding of Christianity came from no such human teacher.\f*
\s1 How he was before
\p 
\v 13 \w You|strong="G3754"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* heard \w of|strong="G2316"\w* \w my|strong="G1699"\w* \w former|strong="G4218"\w* conduct \w while|strong="G1722"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Judaism|strong="G2454"\w*, \w how|strong="G3754"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* rabid \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w my|strong="G1699"\w* \w persecution|strong="G1377"\w* \w of|strong="G2316"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*'s \w Church|strong="G1577"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* tried \w to|strong="G2532"\w* annihilate \w it|strong="G2532"\w*;
\v 14 \w indeed|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w advancing|strong="G4298"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Judaism|strong="G2454"\w* \w beyond|strong="G5228"\w* \w many|strong="G4183"\w* Jews \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w my|strong="G1722"\w* own age, \w being|strong="G5225"\w* \w far|strong="G3588"\w* \w more|strong="G4183"\w* \w zealous|strong="G2207"\w* \w for|strong="G5228"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w traditions|strong="G3862"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w my|strong="G1722"\w* forefathers.
