\v 18 Subsequently, \w after|strong="G3326"\w* \w three|strong="G5140"\w* \w years|strong="G2094"\w*,\f + \fr 1:18 \ft The Text does not say that he spent three years in Arabia; part of the time he was in Damascus.\f* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w went|strong="G2532"\w* \w up|strong="G1519"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w Jerusalem|strong="G2414"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* compare notes \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w Peter|strong="G2532"\w*,\f + \fr 1:18 \ft 98% of the Greek manuscripts have “Peter”, not ‘Cephas’. In 2:1 below it is 93%.\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w stayed|strong="G1961"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w him|strong="G2532"\w* \w fifteen|strong="G1178"\w* \w days|strong="G2250"\w*.
