\c 2
\s1 How he was recognized by the apostolate
\m 
\v 1 \w Fourteen|strong="G1180"\w* \w years|strong="G2094"\w* \w later|strong="G3326"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w went|strong="G2532"\w* \w up|strong="G1519"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w Jerusalem|strong="G2414"\w* \w again|strong="G3825"\w*, \w with|strong="G3326"\w* Barnabas, \w taking|strong="G4838"\w* \w Titus|strong="G5103"\w* \w along|strong="G2532"\w* \w as|strong="G1519"\w* \w well|strong="G2532"\w*.
\v 2 \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w went|strong="G2532"\w* \w on|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w basis|strong="G2596"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* revelation \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w set|strong="G2532"\w* \w before|strong="G1722"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* [\w the|strong="G1722"\w* main apostles] \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Gospel|strong="G2098"\w* \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w proclaim|strong="G2784"\w* \w among|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w nations|strong="G1484"\w*/\w Gentiles|strong="G1484"\w*.\f + \fr 2:2 \ft This event is described in more detail in Acts chapter 15, where verse 3 says they were “sent on their way by the church”. Here Paul says he went “on the basis of a revelation”—I suppose he is referring mainly to the content of what he set before the apostles and elders. I gather that Paul and Barnabas had a closed session with James, Peter and John before going to the whole assembly.\f*—\w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w did|strong="G2532"\w* \w this|strong="G3588"\w* \w privately|strong="G2398"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w with|strong="G1722"\w* influence, \w lest|strong="G3361"\w* somehow \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w might|strong="G2532"\w* \w run|strong="G5143"\w*, \w or|strong="G2228"\w* \w had|strong="G2532"\w* \w run|strong="G5143"\w*, \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w vain|strong="G2756"\w*.
\v 3 However, \w not|strong="G3761"\w* \w even|strong="G3761"\w* \w Titus|strong="G5103"\w*, \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w with|strong="G4862"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*, \w was|strong="G1510"\w* compelled \w to|strong="G1510"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w circumcised|strong="G4059"\w*, \w for|strong="G3761"\w* \w being|strong="G1510"\w* \w a|strong="G1510"\w* \w Greek|strong="G1672"\w*.
\v 4 \w This|strong="G3588"\w* \w came|strong="G3588"\w* \w up|strong="G1722"\w* \w because|strong="G1223"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w false|strong="G5569"\w* brothers \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w were|strong="G3588"\w* smuggled \w in|strong="G1722"\w*\f + \fr 2:4 \ft Who was responsible for the smuggling? And in whose service were they, really, even though they were evidently part of the Christian community?\f* (\w who|strong="G3739"\w* stole \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w spy|strong="G2684"\w* \w out|strong="G2684"\w* \w our|strong="G2424"\w* \w freedom|strong="G1657"\w*, \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w we|strong="G2249"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w*, \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w as|strong="G1722"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* reduce \w us|strong="G2249"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* slavery),
