\v 18 “Now \w if|strong="G1487"\w* \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w rebuild|strong="G3618"\w* \w the|strong="G1063"\w* \w things|strong="G3778"\w* \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w destroyed|strong="G2647"\w*, \w I|strong="G3739"\w* acknowledge \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w I|strong="G3739"\w* am \w a|strong="G1487"\w* \w transgressor|strong="G3848"\w*.\f + \fr 2:18 \ft Whereas he had once tried to destroy the Church, he is now building it, which amounts to recognizing that he had been wrong before, a transgressor.\f*
\v 19 \w For|strong="G1063"\w* \w through|strong="G1223"\w* \w the|strong="G1223"\w* \w law|strong="G3551"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* died \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w the|strong="G1223"\w* \w law|strong="G3551"\w* \w in|strong="G2316"\w* \w order|strong="G2443"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w live|strong="G2198"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*.\f + \fr 2:19 \ft He thought he was serving God before, persecuting the Church in his zeal for the law. But ‘the law’ crucified Christ, and in declaring allegiance to the crucified Christ he died to the law, so that he could really live for God. Galatians 4:4 says that the Son was “born under law”.\f*
\v 20 \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w been|strong="G2532"\w* \w crucified|strong="G4957"\w* \w with|strong="G1722"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*, \w so|strong="G2532"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w no|strong="G3765"\w* \w longer|strong="G3765"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w live|strong="G2198"\w* \w but|strong="G1161"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w lives|strong="G2198"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*; \w what|strong="G3739"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w now|strong="G1161"\w* \w live|strong="G2198"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w this|strong="G3588"\w* \w body|strong="G4561"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w live|strong="G2198"\w* \w by|strong="G1722"\w* \w faith|strong="G4102"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Son|strong="G5207"\w* \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*, \w who|strong="G3739"\w* loved \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w gave|strong="G3860"\w* \w Himself|strong="G1438"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w my|strong="G1722"\w* \w place|strong="G1722"\w*.\f + \fr 2:20 \ft A tremendous statement, and when we allow it to function in our lives it is an equally tremendous truth! Those who try to live the Christian life in their own strength generally make a poor job of it; when I allow Christ to live His life through me He makes a good job of it (to the extent that I stay out of the way).\f*
\v 21 \w I|strong="G1063"\w* \w do|strong="G1223"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* nullify \w the|strong="G1223"\w* \w grace|strong="G5485"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*; \w for|strong="G1063"\w* \w if|strong="G1487"\w* \w righteousness|strong="G1343"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w through|strong="G1223"\w* \w the|strong="G1223"\w* \w law|strong="G3551"\w*, \w then|strong="G1063"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w died|strong="G3588"\w* \w for|strong="G1063"\w* \w nothing|strong="G3756"\w*!”\f + \fr 2:21 \ft This is a very serious statement! Anyone who can save himself does not need Christ's sacrifice.\f*
\c 3
\ms1 Law or faith
\m 
\v 1 \w O|strong="G5599"\w* foolish \w Galatians|strong="G1052"\w*! \w Who|strong="G3739"\w* \w has|strong="G5101"\w* bewitched \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w not|strong="G3739"\w* \w be|strong="G5547"\w* persuaded \w by|strong="G2596"\w* \w the|strong="G2596"\w* Truth\f + \fr 3:1 \ft Perhaps 3% of the Greek manuscripts omit “that you not be persuaded by the Truth” (as in NIV, NASB, LB, TEV, etc.), which weakens the statement considerably.\f*—\w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w was|strong="G2424"\w* clearly \w portrayed|strong="G4270"\w* \w among|strong="G2596"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w as|strong="G2596"\w* having \w been|strong="G5547"\w* \w crucified|strong="G4717"\w*, \w before|strong="G2596"\w* \w your|strong="G5210"\w* \w very|strong="G4771"\w* \w eyes|strong="G3788"\w*!\f + \fr 3:1 \ft It almost sounds like there was a dramatic demonstration.\f*
\v 2 \w Just|strong="G3440"\w* tell \w me|strong="G2983"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w thing|strong="G3778"\w*: \w Did|strong="G3588"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w receive|strong="G2983"\w* \w the|strong="G1537"\w* \w Spirit|strong="G4151"\w* \w by|strong="G1537"\w* \w works|strong="G2041"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w law|strong="G3551"\w*, \w or|strong="G2228"\w* \w by|strong="G1537"\w* hearing \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w faith|strong="G4102"\w*?
\v 3 Can \w you|strong="G1510"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w so|strong="G3779"\w* foolish? \w Having|strong="G4151"\w* \w begun|strong="G1728"\w* \w in|strong="G4151"\w* \w spirit|strong="G4151"\w*, \w do|strong="G1510"\w* \w you|strong="G1510"\w* \w finish|strong="G2005"\w* \w in|strong="G4151"\w* \w flesh|strong="G4561"\w*?
\v 4 \w Have|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G1487"\w* \w suffered|strong="G3958"\w* \w so|strong="G2532"\w* \w much|strong="G5118"\w* \w for|strong="G2532"\w* \w nothing|strong="G1500"\w*—\w if|strong="G1487"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* really \w was|strong="G2532"\w* \w for|strong="G2532"\w* \w nothing|strong="G1500"\w*?
\v 5 \w Furthermore|strong="G2532"\w*, \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w supplies|strong="G2023"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Spirit|strong="G4151"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w works|strong="G2041"\w* \w miracles|strong="G1411"\w* \w among|strong="G1722"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*, \it is He activated\it* \w by|strong="G1722"\w* \w works|strong="G2041"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w law|strong="G3551"\w*, \w or|strong="G2228"\w* \w by|strong="G1722"\w* hearing \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w faith|strong="G4102"\w*?\f + \fr 3:5 \ft Although I have capitalized the pronoun, there must have been a human being involved as well.\f*—
\v 6 \w just|strong="G2531"\w* \w as|strong="G2531"\w* \w Abraham|strong="G4100"\w* ‘\w believed|strong="G4100"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w credited|strong="G3049"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w* \w as|strong="G2531"\w* \w righteousness|strong="G1343"\w*.’\f + \fr 3:6 \ft This is a quote from Genesis 15:6, but is not presented as such.\f*
\p 
\v 7 \w Now|strong="G1510"\w* \w you|strong="G3754"\w* \w must|strong="G1510"\w* \w know|strong="G1097"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* only \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w faith|strong="G4102"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* ‘\w sons|strong="G5207"\w*’ \w of|strong="G1537"\w* Abraham.
\v 8 Further, \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Scripture|strong="G1124"\w*, foreseeing \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w would|strong="G2316"\w* \w justify|strong="G1344"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w nations|strong="G1484"\w* \w by|strong="G1722"\w* \w faith|strong="G4102"\w*,\f + \fr 3:8 \ft The form of the verb is ambiguous as to mood; it could be either Indicative or Subjunctive. The Indicative would give a direct quote, “God justifies the nations by faith”, but we don't find this quote in the OT, so I chose the Subjunctive. Notice that ‘the Scripture’ is personified! It/He sees/knows in advance what God is going to do.\f* proclaimed \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Gospel|strong="G4283"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* advance \w to|strong="G1722"\w* Abraham: “\w All|strong="G3956"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w nations|strong="G1484"\w* \w will|strong="G2316"\w* \w be|strong="G3956"\w* \w blessed|strong="G1757"\w* \w through|strong="G1722"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w*.”\f + \fr 3:8 \ft This is a direct quote from Genesis 12:3, which, of course, had not been written yet in Abraham's day (in his day the only written Scripture available was the book of Job). Notice that the personification of ‘Scripture’ continues; It/He is the One who said this to Abraham, so all we need to do is go back to Genesis to find out who it is—Jehovah Himself, presumably the Son!\f*
\v 9 \w So|strong="G5620"\w* \w then|strong="G5620"\w*, \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w faith|strong="G4102"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w blessed|strong="G2127"\w* \w along|strong="G4862"\w* \w with|strong="G4862"\w* Abraham, \w the|strong="G1537"\w* \w faithful|strong="G4103"\w*.
\s1 The curse of the law
