\v 17 Further, \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w say|strong="G3004"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w*: \w a|strong="G1096"\w* \w covenant|strong="G1242"\w* confirmed beforehand \w by|strong="G5259"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w in|strong="G1519"\w* Christ\f + \fr 3:17 \ft Less than 3% of the Greek manuscripts, of inferior quality, omit “in Christ” (as in NIV, NASB, LB, TEV, etc.). Without Christ, the Seed, there would have been no promise. The incarnation of Jehovah the Son was in the Plan before the creation of this world (1 Peter 1:19-20).\f* \w cannot|strong="G3756"\w* \w be|strong="G1096"\w* annulled \w by|strong="G5259"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w law|strong="G3551"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w came|strong="G1096"\w* \w four|strong="G5071"\w* \w hundred|strong="G5071"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w thirty|strong="G5144"\w* \w years|strong="G2094"\w* \w later|strong="G3326"\w*,\f + \fr 3:17 \ft Abraham left Haran in 1921 \sc bc\sc*, when he was 75. The Exodus occurred in 1491 \sc bc\sc*. 1921 – 1491 = 430. For an explanation of these dates see the excellent discussion by Floyd Nolen Jones in his \it Chronology of the Old Testament: A Return to the Basics\it*, Kings Word Press, 1999 (14\sup th\sup* edition).\f* \w so|strong="G2532"\w* \w as|strong="G1519"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w make|strong="G2673"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w promise|strong="G1860"\w* \w of|strong="G5259"\w* \w no|strong="G3756"\w* \w effect|strong="G2673"\w*.
