\v 27 \w As|strong="G3745"\w* \w many|strong="G3745"\w* \w of|strong="G1519"\w* \w you|strong="G3745"\w* \w as|strong="G3745"\w* \w were|strong="G3745"\w* baptized \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*\f + \fr 3:27 \ft See 1 Corinthians 12:13.\f* \w have|strong="G3745"\w* \w clothed|strong="G1746"\w* yourselves \w with|strong="G1519"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*
\v 28 —\w there|strong="G2532"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w neither|strong="G3761"\w* \w Jew|strong="G2453"\w* \w nor|strong="G3761"\w* \w Greek|strong="G1672"\w*, \w there|strong="G2532"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w neither|strong="G3761"\w* \w slave|strong="G1401"\w* \w nor|strong="G3761"\w* \w free|strong="G1658"\w*, \w there|strong="G2532"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w no|strong="G3756"\w* ‘male \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w female|strong="G2338"\w*’;\f + \fr 3:28 \ft The Text does not have ‘neither male nor female’; the formula changes, as I have indicated. I suppose the reference is to Genesis 1:27, and the reason for the female in Genesis 2:18. All are saved on the same basis.\f* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w one|strong="G1520"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w*\f + \fr 3:28 \ft The reference is to the spiritual realm, not the physical—a Jew who believes into Jesus does not stop being a physical Jew, a slave who believes into Jesus does not automatically change social status, a male who believes into Jesus does not stop being a physical male, etc. But if we are all “clothed with Christ”, verse 27, we will all look alike, at least from a distance. People looking at us should think they are looking at Him.\f*—
\v 29 \w so|strong="G1161"\w* \w if|strong="G1487"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*'s, \w then|strong="G1161"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* Abraham's \w seed|strong="G4690"\w*\f + \fr 3:29 \ft Abraham's seed, not Jacob's.\f* \w and|strong="G1161"\w* \w heirs|strong="G2818"\w* \w according|strong="G2596"\w* \w to|strong="G2596"\w* \w the|strong="G1161"\w* \w promise|strong="G1860"\w*.
\c 4
\s1 Sons or slaves
\m 
\v 1 \w To|strong="G1909"\w* proceed, \w as|strong="G3745"\w* \w long|strong="G5550"\w* \w as|strong="G3745"\w* \w the|strong="G3956"\w* \w heir|strong="G2818"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w a|strong="G1510"\w* \w child|strong="G3516"\w*, \w he|strong="G1161"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w no|strong="G3762"\w* \w different|strong="G1308"\w* \w from|strong="G3588"\w* \w a|strong="G1510"\w* \w slave|strong="G1401"\w*, \w though|strong="G1161"\w* \w he|strong="G1161"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w owner|strong="G2962"\w* \w of|strong="G2962"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w*,
\v 2 \w but|strong="G2532"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w under|strong="G5259"\w* \w guardians|strong="G2012"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w stewards|strong="G3623"\w* \w until|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* time \w appointed|strong="G4287"\w* \w by|strong="G5259"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w father|strong="G3962"\w*.
\v 3 Similarly, \w when|strong="G3753"\w* \w we|strong="G2249"\w* \w were|strong="G1510"\w* \w children|strong="G3516"\w* \w we|strong="G2249"\w* \w were|strong="G1510"\w* \w in|strong="G2532"\w* \w slavery|strong="G1398"\w* \w under|strong="G5259"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* basic \w principles|strong="G4747"\w* \w of|strong="G5259"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w world|strong="G2889"\w*.\f + \fr 4:3 \ft The only true freedom available in this life is to be a slave of Jesus Christ. In John 8:34 the Lord Jesus said, “whoever commits sin is a slave of sin”, and in verse 36, “if the Son makes you free, you will be free indeed”. Sin gives Satan an entrance, and he has various instruments for binding people (see verse 8 below).\f*
\v 4 \w But|strong="G1161"\w* \w at|strong="G1537"\w* \w just|strong="G3588"\w* \w the|strong="G1537"\w* right \w time|strong="G5550"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w sent|strong="G1821"\w* \w out|strong="G1537"\w* \w His|strong="G3588"\w* \w Son|strong="G5207"\w*, \w born|strong="G1096"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w a|strong="G1096"\w* \w woman|strong="G1135"\w*, \w born|strong="G1096"\w* \w under|strong="G5259"\w* \w law|strong="G3551"\w*,
\v 5 \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w He|strong="G3588"\w* might \w redeem|strong="G1805"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w under|strong="G5259"\w* \w law|strong="G3551"\w*, \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w we|strong="G2443"\w* might receive \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w adoption|strong="G5206"\w* \w as|strong="G5206"\w* \w sons|strong="G5206"\w*.
\v 6 \w And|strong="G1161"\w* \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w you|strong="G3754"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w sons|strong="G5207"\w*,\f + \fr 4:6 \ft If you have the Holy Spirit in your heart, it is because you have been adopted into God's family; you are a ‘son’.\f* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w sent|strong="G1821"\w* \w out|strong="G2896"\w* \w the|strong="G1519"\w* \w Spirit|strong="G4151"\w* \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w His|strong="G1519"\w* \w Son|strong="G5207"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w your|strong="G3588"\w*\f + \fr 4:6 \ft Perhaps 6% of the Greek manuscripts read ‘our’ instead of “your”, setting up a conflict with the verb “you are” at the beginning of the verse (as in NIV, NASB, TEV, etc.).\f* \w hearts|strong="G2588"\w*, calling, “Abba, \w Father|strong="G3962"\w*”.\f + \fr 4:6 \ft “Father” is a translation of “Abba”.\f*
\v 7 \w Therefore|strong="G1223"\w* \w you|strong="G1487"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w no|strong="G3765"\w* \w longer|strong="G3765"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w slave|strong="G1401"\w* \w but|strong="G1161"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w son|strong="G5207"\w*,\f + \fr 4:7 \ft Here Paul switches from plural to singular.\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w if|strong="G1487"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w son|strong="G5207"\w*, \w also|strong="G2532"\w* \w an|strong="G2532"\w* \w heir|strong="G2818"\w* \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w through|strong="G1223"\w* Christ.\f + \fr 4:7 \ft Evidently 1½% of the Greek manuscripts, of inferior quality, read “through God” instead of “of God through Christ” (as in NIV, NASB, LB, TEV, etc.). Romans 8:17 says we are “heirs of God and joint heirs with Christ”.\f*
\s1 Paul's concern
\p 
