\p 
\v 17 \w They|strong="G2443"\w* zealously court \w you|strong="G5210"\w*\f + \fr 4:17 \ft Paul contrasts himself with the proselytizers: he tells them the truth, even if unpleasant; they start by ‘buttering up’ their intended victims, but then move to create a dependency so they can control them.\f*—\w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w for|strong="G2443"\w* \w good|strong="G2573"\w* \w but|strong="G1438"\w* \w intending|strong="G2309"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* isolate \w you|strong="G5210"\w*, \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w may|strong="G2443"\w* \w seek|strong="G2206"\w* \w them|strong="G1438"\w*.
