\q1 \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* abandoned \w woman|strong="G2192"\w* \w has|strong="G2192"\w* \w many|strong="G4183"\w* \w more|strong="G3123"\w* \w children|strong="G5043"\w*
\q2 \w than|strong="G2228"\w* \w she|strong="G2532"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w has|strong="G2192"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* husband.”\f + \fr 4:27 \ft The quote is from Isaiah 54:1—in that chapter Jehovah is telling Israel, His abandoned ‘wife’, that He is going to take her back, restore her, and her future felicity will make her forget the pain of rejection. However, that restoration will presumably be based on the new covenant (Jeremiah 31), as is Christ's Gospel.\f*
\m 
