\c 5
\ms1 Freedom in Christ
\m 
\v 1 \w Stand|strong="G4739"\w* \w firm|strong="G4739"\w* \w therefore|strong="G3767"\w* \w in|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w freedom|strong="G1657"\w* \w with|strong="G2532"\w* \w which|strong="G3588"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w has|strong="G5547"\w* \w made|strong="G1659"\w* \w us|strong="G2249"\w* \w free|strong="G1659"\w*,\f + \fr 5:1 \ft 6-7% of the Greek manuscripts replace this first half of the verse with, “for freedom Christ has made us free; stand firm therefore” (as in NIV, NASB, LB, TEV, etc.).\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w do|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* burdened \w again|strong="G3825"\w* \w with|strong="G2532"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w yoke|strong="G2218"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w slavery|strong="G1397"\w*.
\v 2 Listen! \w I|strong="G1473"\w*, \w Paul|strong="G3972"\w*, \w say|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G3004"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w if|strong="G1437"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* get \w circumcised|strong="G4059"\w*, \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w will|strong="G1473"\w* \w profit|strong="G5623"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w nothing|strong="G3762"\w*.
\v 3 Further, \w I|strong="G1161"\w* \w testify|strong="G3143"\w* \w again|strong="G3825"\w* \w to|strong="G1161"\w* \w every|strong="G3956"\w* \w man|strong="G3956"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* gets \w circumcised|strong="G4059"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w he|strong="G1161"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w obligated|strong="G3781"\w* \w to|strong="G1161"\w* \w keep|strong="G4160"\w* \w the|strong="G3956"\w* \w whole|strong="G3650"\w* \w law|strong="G3551"\w*.\f + \fr 5:3 \ft In the context it is clear that Paul is not decrying physical circumcision, that has an important side benefit—women with circumcised husbands don't get cervical cancer. He is combating the idea of spiritual benefit from the practice, as claimed by the Judaizers, and in particular the ‘necessity’ that they claimed. The procedure is for eight-day-old babies, not adult men.\f*
\v 4 \w You|strong="G1722"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* ‘\w being|strong="G5547"\w* \w justified|strong="G1344"\w*’ \w by|strong="G1722"\w* \w law|strong="G3551"\w* \w have|strong="G3748"\w* \w been|strong="G5547"\w* alienated \w from|strong="G3588"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*; \w you|strong="G1722"\w* \w have|strong="G3748"\w* \w fallen|strong="G1601"\w* \w away|strong="G2673"\w* \w from|strong="G3588"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w grace|strong="G5485"\w*.\f + \fr 5:4 \ft They have regressed from the covenant of grace to the covenant of law.\f*
\v 5 \w For|strong="G1063"\w* \w we|strong="G2249"\w* \w through|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1537"\w* \w Spirit|strong="G4151"\w* eagerly \w wait|strong="G4151"\w*\f + \fr 5:5 \ft “Eagerly wait for”—I love it! Those who are trying to be justified by works don't ‘eagerly wait’ for anything; the future accounting is a source of apprehension. On the other hand, we who understand that we are justified by faith in the Christ do indeed have a hope we can ‘eagerly wait’ for.\f* \w for|strong="G1063"\w* \w the|strong="G1537"\w* \w hope|strong="G1680"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w righteousness|strong="G1343"\w* \w by|strong="G1537"\w* \w faith|strong="G4102"\w*.
\v 6 \w Because|strong="G1223"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w neither|strong="G3777"\w* \w circumcision|strong="G4061"\w* \w nor|strong="G3777"\w* uncircumcision avails \w anything|strong="G5100"\w*, \w but|strong="G1063"\w* \w faith|strong="G4102"\w* \w working|strong="G1754"\w* \w through|strong="G1223"\w* love.
\p 
