\v 13 \w For|strong="G1063"\w* \w not|strong="G3761"\w* \w even|strong="G3761"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w circumcised|strong="G4059"\w* \w keep|strong="G5442"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w law|strong="G3551"\w* \w themselves|strong="G1722"\w*, \w yet|strong="G1063"\w* \w they|strong="G3588"\w* \w want|strong="G2309"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w be|strong="G3588"\w* \w circumcised|strong="G4059"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w they|strong="G3588"\w* \w may|strong="G2443"\w* \w boast|strong="G2744"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w your|strong="G5212"\w* \w flesh|strong="G4561"\w*.\f + \fr 6:13 \ft Again Paul makes clear that he is referring to the religious exercise when practiced on adults, not the physical fact (that is properly practiced on eight-day-old babies).\f*
\v 14 \w But|strong="G1161"\w* \w as|strong="G1722"\w* \w for|strong="G1223"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*, \w may|strong="G2889"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w never|strong="G3361"\w* \w boast|strong="G2744"\w* \w except|strong="G1487"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w cross|strong="G4716"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w our|strong="G2424"\w* \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*, \w through|strong="G1223"\w* \w which|strong="G3739"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w world|strong="G2889"\w* \w has|strong="G2962"\w* \w been|strong="G1096"\w* \w crucified|strong="G4717"\w* \w to|strong="G1722"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*, \w and|strong="G1161"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w to|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w world|strong="G2889"\w*.
\v 15 \w Because|strong="G1063"\w* \w in|strong="G1063"\w* Christ \w Jesus|strong="G1510"\w*\f + \fr 6:15 \ft Some 3% of the Greek manuscripts omit “because in Christ Jesus” (as in NIV, NASB, LB, TEV, etc.).\f* \w neither|strong="G3777"\w* \w circumcision|strong="G4061"\w* \w nor|strong="G3777"\w* uncircumcision avails \w anything|strong="G5100"\w*, \w but|strong="G1063"\w* \w a|strong="G1510"\w* \w new|strong="G2537"\w* \w creation|strong="G2937"\w*.\f + \fr 6:15 \ft If you are not a new creation, you are not saved.\f*
\v 16 \w Now|strong="G2532"\w* \w as|strong="G3745"\w* \w for|strong="G1909"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* conform \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w rule|strong="G2583"\w*, \w peace|strong="G1515"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w mercy|strong="G1656"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* \w upon|strong="G1909"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w upon|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Israel|strong="G2474"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*.\f + \fr 6:16 \ft According to Greek grammar, the repetition of the preposition ‘upon’ in two phrases joined by ‘and’ makes clear that the objects of the prepositions refer to distinct entities. Hence, “the Israel of God” cannot be a reference to the Church, assuming that “those who conform to this rule” refers to those who are “in Christ Jesus”. I take “the Israel of God” to refer to sincere, devout Israelites.\f*
\p 
\v 17 \w Finally|strong="G3064"\w*, \w let|strong="G3930"\w* \w no|strong="G3367"\w* \w one|strong="G3367"\w* \w cause|strong="G3930"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w trouble|strong="G2873"\w*, \w for|strong="G1063"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* bear \w on|strong="G1722"\w* \w my|strong="G1722"\w* \w body|strong="G4983"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* brand \w marks|strong="G4742"\w* \w of|strong="G4983"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Lord|strong="G3588"\w*\f + \fr 6:17 \ft Perhaps 1% of the Greek manuscripts, of inferior quality, omit “Lord” (as in NIV, NASB, LB, TEV, etc.). I would say that the eclectic Greek text that these modern versions generally follow is mistaken at over eighty (80) points in Galatians, of which I mentioned only twelve (mainly the more serious ones).\f* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w*.\f + \fr 6:17 \ft This is an interesting claim. I suppose him to be saying that he deserves respectful treatment because of what he has suffered for Christ's cause.\f*
\s1 Sign-off
\p 
\v 18 \w The|strong="G3588"\w* \w grace|strong="G5485"\w* \w of|strong="G4151"\w* \w our|strong="G2424"\w* \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w be|strong="G3588"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w your|strong="G2962"\w* \w spirit|strong="G4151"\w*, brothers. Amen. 
